5) Per‑event algorithm (CREATE vs MODIFY)

5.1 Load config once (per function instance)
	•	Read config/<cosmosContainer>/tracked-fields.json from Blob into memory (cache with last‑read ETag to avoid repeated downloads).

5.2 For each item from change feed
	1.	Parse raw JSON to ObjectNode newDoc; get docId = newDoc["id"].
	2.	Read current mirror (if exists):
	•	blob = data/<cosmosContainer>/<docId>.json
	•	If exists → get prevETag and baseline = read(blob).
	•	If not → baseline = null (→ CREATE case).
	3.	Decide CREATE/MODIFY
	•	isCreate = (baseline == null)
	4.	Compute deltas on tracked fields (only if MODIFY)
	•	deltas = computeDelta(baseline, newDoc, trackedPaths)
	•	shouldNotify = !deltas.isEmpty()
	•	For AND rules: if any rule field changed, evaluate rule on newDoc.
	5.	Build & send message (only when required)
	•	eventType = isCreate ? "CREATE" : "MODIFY"
	•	messageId = eventType + ":" + cosmosContainer + ":" + docId + ":" + newDoc["_ts"]
	•	Send to Service Bus (duplicate detection will drop dupes).
	6.	Always refresh mirror (even if no notify)
	•	Serialize newDoc (pretty).
	•	Overwrite data/<cosmosContainer>/<docId>.json with ETag If‑Match:
	•	If prevETag != null, set If-Match = prevETag.
	•	If it’s CREATE, use If-None-Match = "*".
	•	(Optional) Store a stable hash in blob metadata (skip write if identical).

Why always refresh? Prevents stale mirrors so future multi‑field AND rules won’t be missed.

⸻

6) Idempotency & retries (production‑safe)
	•	Service Bus: set MessageId as above; turn on duplicate detection.
	•	Blob writes:
	•	CREATE → If-None-Match="*" (safe if another instance created first).
	•	MODIFY → If-Match=prevETag; on 412 Precondition Failed, reload + retry once.
	•	Exceptions:
	•	If sending to Service Bus fails, do not write the mirror; let Functions retry the whole batch.
	•	If sending succeeds but mirror write fails → throw RuntimeException so the batch retries; Service Bus dedupe prevents a duplicate notification.

⸻

7) Minimal code skeleton (call sequence)

// parse doc
ObjectNode newDoc = MAPPER.readTree(json).deepCopy();
String docId = newDoc.path("id").asText(null);
if (docId == null) return;

// read mirror if exists
BlobClient mirror = DATA.container("data")
    .getBlobClient(cosmosContainer + "/" + docId + ".json");

ObjectNode baseline = null;
String prevETag = null;
if (mirror.exists()) {
    BlobProperties p = mirror.getProperties();
    prevETag = p.getETag();
    baseline = (ObjectNode) MAPPER.readTree(mirror.downloadContent().toBytes());
}

// decide notify
boolean shouldNotify = false;
String eventType = (baseline == null) ? "CREATE" : "MODIFY";

if ("CREATE".equals(eventType)) {
    shouldNotify = RuleEvaluator.evaluateOnNewDoc(newDoc); // your AND rules
} else {
    var deltas = Delta.compute(baseline, newDoc, trackedPaths);
    boolean anyRuleFieldChanged = Delta.anyRuleFieldChanged(deltas, ruleFields);
    shouldNotify = anyRuleFieldChanged && RuleEvaluator.evaluateOnNewDoc(newDoc);
}

// send message if required
if (shouldNotify) {
    ServiceBusMessage msg = MessageFactory.build(newDoc, baseline, eventType, cosmosContainer);
    msg.setMessageId(eventType + ":" + cosmosContainer + ":" + docId + ":" + newDoc.path("_ts").asText(""));
    busSender.sendMessage(msg);
}

// ALWAYS refresh mirror (idempotent)
if (baseline == null) {
    // create
    BlobRequestConditions c = new BlobRequestConditions().setIfNoneMatch("*");
    mirror.uploadWithResponse(
        new BlockBlobSimpleUploadOptions(BinaryData.fromString(pretty(newDoc)))
            .setRequestConditions(c),
        null, Context.NONE);
} else {
    // overwrite with If-Match
    BlobRequestConditions c = new BlobRequestConditions().setIfMatch(prevETag);
    mirror.uploadWithResponse(
        new BlockBlobSimpleUploadOptions(BinaryData.fromString(pretty(newDoc)))
            .setRequestConditions(c),
        null, Context.NONE);
}


